# Keep the Docker build context small and reproducible. The Dockerfile
# does `COPY . .` in the backend stage, so anything not excluded here
# gets shipped to the daemon and is visible to that COPY layer. CI
# builds via actions/checkout (tracked files only) are unaffected; this
# matters mostly for local `docker build` runs where the working tree
# has live state under data/, .devlogs/, etc.

# Version control + GitHub metadata — not needed in the image
.git/
.gitignore
.gitattributes
.github/

# Local-only runtime + dev artifacts that must NEVER end up in a build
# layer (live SQLite, encryption key file, secrets, dev logs)
data/
secrets/
.devlogs/
.claude/
bin/

# IDE / OS noise
.vscode/
.idea/
*.swp
.DS_Store

# Local env files (never committed, never shipped)
.env
.env.*

# Frontend build output and dependencies — Dockerfile builds these
# fresh from web/ in the frontend stage, then copies dist/ in via
# --from=frontend, so the checked-in cmd/shellyctl/dist bundle and
# any local web/node_modules / web/dist are noise.
web/node_modules/
web/dist/
web/.playwright/
web/test-results/
web/playwright-report/
web/blob-report/
cmd/shellyctl/dist/

# Top-level docs — not embedded, not needed at runtime
*.md
docs/
CHANGELOG.md
LICENSE

# Test / coverage artifacts
coverage.out
*.test
